The simplest way to call jSocial is this:
$(YOUR_DIV).jsocial();

Please note that Google + does not work in IE7. This is not a bug with the plugin
it's just that Google never produced a version that worked with it.

You can also set the options below to customise what's shown:

debug: false,				// If set to true outputs various bits so console.log
insert: 'bottom',			// Insert buttons to top or bottom of div
showTwitter: true,			// Shows Twitter
showDigg: true,				// Shows Sigg
showGooglePlus: true,			// Shows Google +
showLinkedIn: true,			// Shows LinkedIn
showFacebook: true,			// Shows Facebook
showAddThis: true,			// Shows AddThis
buttonLayout: 'vertical',  		// Layout either: horizontal, vertical, nocounter
addThisLayout: 'addthis_counter',	// Can override the button layouts set in buttonLayout
twitterLayout: 'vertical',		// Can override the button layouts set in buttonLayout
googlePlusLayout: 'tall',		// Can override the button layouts set in buttonLayout
diggLayout: 'DiggMedium',		// Can override the button layouts set in buttonLayout
linkedinLayout: 'top',			// Can override the button layouts set in buttonLayout
facebookLayout: 'box_count',		// Can override the button layouts set in buttonLayout
faceBookSend: true,			// Adds the Facebook Send button
facebookShowFaces: false   		// Sets the FB show faces options

